<H3> <TI>   Japan Environmental News Update (1-15 September 1993) </TI></H3>
<H4>   Electric Power Development To Conduct Desulphurization 
Testing in China </H4>
<F P=102> 946C3801C Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 2 Sep 93 p 
10--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 946C3801C </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Complete text of article obtained through NIKKEI BIZ </F>
DATABASE] 
  [Text] On 1 September, Electric Power Development announced 
that it had reached an agreement with the Chinese government to 
conduct demonstration testing of desulphurization technology at 
a coal-burning thermal power plant in Shanxi. A low-cost 
desulphurization facility will be constructed beginning in FY94. 
The project is intended to provide environmental technologies to 
China and for Japan to accumulate technologies for using coal 
with high levels of sulfur content. 
  The testing will be conducted at Unit No 12, Taiyuan Power 
Plant No 1, with an output of 300,000 kilowatts, located in 
Taiyuan, Shanxi. The demonstration testing, commissioned by the 
Ministry of International Trade and Industry, will be 
implemented by Electric Power Development. This is the second 
such project, following that at the Qingdao Power Plant, 
Qingdao, Shandong. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

