<H3> <TI>   Japan Environmental News Update (1-15 September 1993) </TI></H3>
<H4>   Initial Requests for Budget Related to Global Environmental 
Protection Increases </H4>
<F P=102> 946C3801F Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 7 Sep 93 p 
5--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> 946C3801F </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Japanese </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Complete text of article obtained through NIKKEI BIZ </F>
DATABASE] 
  [Text] The Environment Ministry summarized the initial 
requests for the FY94 budget for global environmental protection 
made by 17 ministries and agencies, including the Environment 
Agency, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and the Science and 
Technology Agency. The total amount requested is &yen;566.2 
billion, an increase of &yen;31.8 billion and 6 percent over 
FY93's actual budget. 
  Concerning individual items, at &yen;445.7 billion, the 
largest amount requested is for the "Development and Spread of 
Technologies for Global Environmental Protection," an increase 
of 3 percent over the previous year. The "Promotion of the 
Development and Use of Nuclear Energy" (Science and Technology 
Agency) is requesting &yen;276.35 billion. Newly requested items 
include the "Establishment of Technological Standards for Gas 
Stations for Low-Pollution Vehicles" and a "Safety Study for a 
Sulfur Sodium Battery," both by the Ministry of Home Affairs. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

