<H3> <TI>   Tests on Cuban Meningitis Vaccine Announced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2411141393 Buenos Aires CLARIN in Spanish 20 Nov 93 p 42 </F>
<F P=103> PY2411141393 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires CLARIN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Paulo Andalo] </F>
  [Excerpt] The government confirmed on 19 November that 
before the end of the year a pilot test will be held to study 
the efficiency of the Cuban vaccine against meningitis in our 
country. 
  The test will be made on 100,000 volunteers younger than 
six. 
The test possibly will concentrate in La Pampa, the province in 
which the disease has caused more deaths so far. The tests will 
begin in a few days after the arrival of the vaccine shipments 
from Cuba. The vaccines already have been approved in other 
countries like Chile. 
  Moises Spitz, director of the Malbran Institute, which is in 
charge of making the tests, told CLARIN: "Blood samples will be 
taken first from those who will be vaccinated, who will be 
children younger than six for the most part, who are the most 
badly affected group. There are more doubts about the efficiency 
of the vaccine at this age. Youths up to 14 years old also will 
be vaccinated." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

