<H3> <TI>   Ahmedabad Jaundice-Affected, 380 Cases </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WE0114A Madras THE HINDU in English 24 Nov 93 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> 94WE0114A </F>
<F P=104>  Madras THE HINDU </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Ahmedabad, Nov 23--The entire walled city of 
Ahmedabad has been declared jaundice-affected and its suburbs 
face the threat of the epidemic, which has affected at least 380 
persons and claimed three lives. 
  The declaration to be gazetted empowers the health 
authorities to force residents replace leaky domestic water 
supply lines, the root-cause for the outbreak of the epidemic, 
contamination of water supply by sewage. 

</TEXT>

