<H3> <TI>   Knesset Publicizes AIDS Figures on International AIDS Day </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2511103593 Tel Aviv HADASHOT in Hebrew 25 Nov 93 p 11 </F>
<F P=103> TA2511103593 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HADASHOT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Hila Tov] </F>
  [Excerpt] Some 50 percent of Israelis who contract AIDS 
belong to the 15-24 age group; 1,084 AIDS carriers are 
registered in Israel, but it is assessed that their real number 
is anywhere between 2,000 to 2,500. The number of those 
suffering from the disease is 255. So far 188 have died from 
AIDS. 
  These figures were revealed yesterday during the Knesset's 
Education and Culture Committee session, marking International 
AIDS Day. Israel is defined by the WHO as a low risk country. 
Switzerland, Spain, and Italy lead Europe in AIDS frequency. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

