<H3> <TI>   More than 2.3 Million Krones Spent on AIDS Treatment </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2812214393 Moscow BALTFAX in English 1949 GMT 28 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD2812214393 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow BALTFAX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] More than 2.3 Mn krones (about $170,000) have been 
spent for the struggle with AIDS in Estonia over the last year. 
This was announced to BALTFAX by a physician of the Tallinn 
Merimetsa Hospital's AIDS Center, Jaan Martin. 
  As many as 29 AIDS victims currently live in Estonia. As 
many as three of the infected left Estonia and two AIDS victims 
died. A total of 5 more AIDS victims were discovered this year. 
The first AIDS victim was discovered in Estonia in 1987. 

</TEXT>

