<H3> <TI>   Porcine Cholera Detected in Havana, Pinar del Rio </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2611231293 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1255 
GMT 26 Nov 93 </F>

<F P=103> FL2611231293 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Porcine cholera, a viral pig disease not observed in 
Cuba since 1974, has been detected in Pinar del Rio and Havana 
Provinces, while Havana City, Matanzas, and Isle of Youth have 
been declared threatened areas. The transportation of pigs 
within and between provinces is not recommended. 

