<H3> <TI>   Total AIDS Cases Reported on AIDS Day </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0212125993 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2250 GMT 1 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD0212125993 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 1 December -- Today is World AIDS Day. 
According to the presidential committee for fighting AIDS, 
there are 87 infected people in Kiev, of whom 27 are Kievites. 
The Ministry of Health Protection reports that there are 141 
registered cases of AIDS in Ukraine, 56 percent of whom are men. 
In total, 12 people have died as a result of AIDS, and four of 
these were children. 

</TEXT>

