<H3> <TI>   Government Statement Cites 149 AIDS Cases on Island </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC3011173293 Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY in English 1620 GMT 
30 Nov 93 </F>

<F P=103> NC3011173293 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Nicosia, Nov 30 (CNA)--Two more Cypriots were 
tested HIV positive in November bringing the total number of 
AIDS cases on the island to 149, an official announcement said 
Tuesday [30 November]. 
  The two new cases involve a 32-year-old woman and a 
35-year-old man. 
  The high risk age group is 20-39 which includes 64 out of 
the 
82 HIV positive Cypriots of the 149 AIDS cases on the island, 67 
involve foreigners. 
[passage omitted] 
  In Cyprus, 12 people have died of AIDS, from a total of 20 
people who developed the disease in full. 

