<H3> <TI>   Submarine Nuclear Fuel Stolen From Murmansk </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0112204693 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1800 GMT 1 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD0112204693 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] When one reads police reports, one forms the 
impression that Russian thieves are the deftest thieves in the 
world. It appears that our correspondent in Murmansk, Valeriy 
Anuchin, is going to confirm this. He reports that someone has 
managed to steal nuclear fuel from one of the depots of the 
Northern Fleet, situated in the outskirts of the city. This was 
the kind of fuel used for nuclear submarines. Three uranium 
rods have disappeared. They pose no threat to [people's] health 
and the environment, and apparently the thieves knew this when 
they were stealing the rods. 

</TEXT>

