<F P=101> RUSSIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Stolen Nuclear Fuel Still Missing </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0812111993 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 7 Dec 93 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> PM0812111993 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Vladimir Gundarov report: "Nuclear Fuel Kept Under </F>
Padlock, Whereas Electronic Security Lock Was Needed"] 
  [Text] The more than 1 kilogram of nuclear fuel intended 
for Northern Fleet submarine reactors whose disappearance from a 
depot in Murmansk was detected on 27 November has not been 
located as of today. 
  "The thieves, who are most probably nuclear specialists, 
knew 
how to remove the so-called core from the coolant elements at 
the actual scene of the crime," Major General of Justice Fedor 
Shepetov, military prosecutor of the Northern Fleet, said. 
"This is the second similar case in the last six months." 

</TEXT>

