<H3> <TI>   Parliament Approves Nuclear Convention, Other Protocols </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WS0112120793 Tallinn BNS in English 1719 GMT 30 Nov 93 </F>
<F P=103> WS0112120793 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Nov 30, BNS -- The Lithuanian parliament 
passed a resolution Tuesday on Lithuania's decision to join the 
May 21, 1963, Vienna convention on the civil responsibility for 
nuclear damage and the joint protocol on the application of the 
Vienna and Paris conventions. 
  The Lithuanian lawmakers also adopted a resolution on 
international agreements dealing with double taxation of income 
and capital, as well as fiscal violations. 

</TEXT>

