<F P=101> UKRAINE </F>
<H3> <TI>   45 Percent of Population Wants Ukraine To Remain Nuclear </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0512034293 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 0130 GMT 
5 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD0512034293 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian Academy of Sciences' institute of 
sociology has carried out a survey among the population. Thus, 
45 percent of people questioned are in favor of Ukraine 
retaining the status of a nuclear state and only a third want 
its nuclear disarmament. The popularity of politicians was also 
unexpected. Former Prime Minister Leonid Kuchma is most popular. 
President Kravchuk is in second place, with Rukh Chairman 
Vyacheslav Chornovil third and Supreme Soviet Chairman Ivan 
Plyushch fourth. However, most consider Leonid Kravchuk 
nevertheless to be the top contender for the new election of 
president. 

</TEXT>

