<H3> <TI>   Uranium-Smuggling Incidents Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   3 Georgians Arrested </H4>
<F P=102> TA2711145093 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1440 GMT 27 Nov 93 </F>
<F P=103> TA2711145093 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bursa, Nov. 27 (AA) -- Police have seized 4.5 kg of 
uranium in this nortwestern city and arrested three Georgians 
trying to sell the material intended for use to produce nuclear 
weapons, officials said on Saturday. 
  They said police, acting on a tipoff that the Georgians who 
came to Turkey about a week ago were looking for a market to 
sell the uranium, contacted them as potential buyers. 
  When police tried to detain the Georgians, a brief clash 
broke out and the sellers were wounded and arrested. 
  The Georgians were asking $150,000 for one kg of uranium. 
  It was not immediately clear how the Georgians acquired the 
uranium but after the collapse of the former Soviet Union there 
have been widespread reports of stolen nuclear materials. 
  The seized uranium was sent to Turkey's Atomic Energy 
Institute for further research. 

</TEXT>

