<H3> <TI>   Russian, Italian Ministers Sign Disarmament Aid Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0212162893 Paris AFP in English 1610 GMT 2 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> AU0212162893 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Rome, Dec 2 (AFP) -- Italy will aid Russia to 
dismantle its nuclear weapons, under an agreement signed here by 
Foreign Ministers Beniamino Andreatta and Andrey Kosyrev, the 
Italian Foreign Ministry said Thursday. 
  The aid will be in the sectors of monitoring the 
environmental and health aspects and protecting the personnel 
carrying out the destruction of the weapons. 
  The agreement, which will cost Italy 10 billion lire (six 
million dollars), has to be ratified by parliament. 
  Kosyrev has been in Rome since Monday for the ministerial 
meeting of the Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe 
(CSCE). 

</TEXT>

