<H3> <TI>   Swedish Authorities Increase Checks After Murmansk Uranium 
Theft </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1012122093 Stockholm Radio Sweden in Swedish 1130 GMT 10 
Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD1012122093 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Swedish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Security police and the customs have increased 
border control in Norrbotten [northeastern province] to stop 
uranium smuggling through Sweden. This is taking place after a 
warning from the Russian police that one kilo of uranium for 
nuclear submarines has been stolen in Murmansk. Saepo chief (Bo 
Beckman) warns that the uranium can come into Sweden. The 
customs is now making random checks of radioactive radiation at 
the borders in the north. 

</TEXT>

