<F P=101> INDIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Surface-to-Surface Medium Range Missile Launched 30 Nov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK3011110993 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 30 Nov 93 </F>

<F P=103> BK3011110993 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The indigenously developed surface-to-surface medium 
range missile Prithvi [Earth] was successfully launched at 1225 
PM [0655 GMT] from the interim test range at Chandipur on sea in 
Orissa today. Prithvi landed accurately after three minutes on 
a small island (Tentuli Chada) located in the Bay of Bengal as 
planned. This was the 12th launch of Prithvi. The speciality 
of today's launch is that it was from mobile launcher with a 250 
kg payload. The scientific adviser to the Defense Ministry, Dr. 
Abdul Kalam, and the three service chiefs witnessed the test 
launch. 

</TEXT>

