<F P=101> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Nuclear Test Reportedly Carried Out in Mediterranean </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0712150393 Cairo AL-SHA'B in Arabic 30 Nov 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC0712150393 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-SHA'B </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Mahmud Bakri] </F>
  [Text] Israel carried out a new nuclear test in the 
Mediterranean early this month. According to our information, 
the new nuclear test focused on experiments with new types of 
short-range nuclear missiles and other technological weapons and 
equipment. 
  An Israeli technical committee chose the site of the new 
nuclear test, preparations for which lasted approximately four 
months. The same information indicates that the test aimed to 
check the efficiency of three secret Israeli bases that control 
the launch of nuclear missiles and weapons. Israel spent over 
$30 million on the test and part of the money was used to buy 
advanced technological equipment. 
  Some Arab governments reportedly received important 
political 
reports on the details of the test. The reports urged these 
governments to intervene directly with the United States and 
European states to keep the Mediterranean safe from nuclear 
tests. 
  This is Israel's second nuclear test this year. 

</TEXT>

