<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister on Signing of NPT, Indian Arms Acquisition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0712033193 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 7 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> BK0712033193 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Asif Ahmad Ali has said that 
Pakistan will not sign the Nuclear Nonproliferation Treaty [NPT] 
in a situation in which India is doing everything for the 
proliferation Aof nuclear weapons. In an interview with a 
Bangladeshi newspaper, THE TELEGRAPH, he said that Pakistan has 
been obliged to face a difficult situation through the linking 
of aid with the signing of the NPT in the Pressler Amendment, 
while India is acquiring nuclear technology and introducing 
weapons to carry nuclear warheads to their targets and [nuclear] 
submarines. 
  The foreign minister said that Pakistan believes in nuclear 
nonproliferation. However, the security issues of relevant 
countries should be viewed from a regional perspective. He 
urged India to review its role in the region. 

</TEXT>

