<H3> <TI>   Serbs Fire `Shells Carrying Chemical Charges' at Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2212094893 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 0900 GMT 22 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> AU2212094893 </F>
<F P=104>  Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The 1st Corps Information Service reports that 
artillery shells fired from Chetnik positions at parts of the 
defense lines suggest that today too will probably see the 
aggressor using all available means to enter the city. 
  This morning, an all-out artillery barrage is being directed 
at the region in and around Zuc, which the [Serbian] aggressor 
is targeting with howitzers, tanks, mortars, and other heavy 
artillery from several positions. The residential areas in the 
northwestern part of the city have also been targeted, while 
shells carrying chemical charges have landed on Glavica. 
  Everything points to the fact that infantry attacks could 
follow, so citizens are warned to restrict (?their movements). 
The general alarm has been sounded and citizens are asked to 
exercise maximum caution. 

</TEXT>

