<H3> <TI>   Angra Nuclear Plant To Resume Operations in January </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1812151993 Sao Paulo VEJA in Portuguese 15 Dec 93 p 51 </F>
<F P=103> PY1812151993 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo VEJA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the ``Radar'' column by Ancelmo Gois] </F>
  [Text] Since it began to operate in March 1982, the Angra 
dos Reis nuclear plant has been idle for a total of 1,937 days. 
This is probably a world record. The Angra dos Reis nuclear 
plant generated its last kilowatt on 5 March. Furnas [Furnas 
Electric Power Plants, Inc.] hopes that its nuclear plant will 
return to life during the second part of January. 

</TEXT>

